<h2>The short version</h2>

<p>NHS gender identity clinic waiting times in England range from roughly <strong>4 to 12+ years</strong> for a first appointment. Scotland is similar or worse. Wales averages around 2 years. The NHS's own target is 18 weeks.</p>

<p>If you're being referred today, you will almost certainly wait years. Most people either go private, self-medicate, or do both while waiting.</p>

<div class="callout callout-blue">
  <p><strong>This is not opinion.</strong> These figures come directly from NHS England, Public Health Scotland, and FOI requests. Every clinic listed below includes a data source.</p>
</div>

<h2>England</h2>

<p>NHS England runs 7 adult Gender Identity Clinics (GICs), with 5 pilot clinics added since 2020. The plan is to have regional services everywhere by 2026-27, but current capacity is nowhere near demand.</p>

